title: Week Seven: What we learned
text:
We are now headed into week eight of the 2015 Arkansas high school football season, and there have been a lot of things I have learned after seven weeks of play in each classification. 
CLASS 7A 
Obviously, Fayetteville isn't invincible. Har-Ber has really turned it on in the past few weeks, and now all of a sudden they are the team to beat in Class 7A. Sure, Fayetteville, Bentonville, and Cabot are solid and I still think Fayetteville has what it takes to win it all, but Har-Ber has already taken out the top two teams in Class 7A.
